values:
too many things to post... August 25th marks the start of a new school year for Clark. for the next two years he will be focusing on school and not taking summers off so he can get it done and over with so we can start our family. Not knowing how much time we will have to do things has us trying to take advantage of the time we have now. We have gone to see quite a few movies (Dark Knight twice!). Went to see Thrice with Circa Survive, and PATD/Motion City Soundtrack/Hush Sound. Just for the record, PATD's new stuff is awful and they are sell outs, but i did rather enjoy their first album and they did put on a terrific show. Moving on... We went on a trip with 13 friends to Newport Beach California. Our friend's dad has a beach house and was kind enough to let us crash there. I had never been to California and it was fantastic! I had also never been to the state of Nevada, so we drove down the strip whilst thinking of Ocean's 11. We have gone on two river rafting trips with the U of U's Outdoor Recreation Program. These trips are organized so well and the price is soo right. The cost includes your food and gas and they provide the equipment. It's interesting to see how people interact with strangers, especially when you have to live with them for a few days. The first was white water rafting the Snake River in Wyoming for three days. You raft a stretch of the river (with awesome rapids) and then pull out and head back to your camp site and do it all over again the next day. The second was five days on the Green River in Desolation Canyon. You raft the river all day and pull over to camp at night until you reach the end. One word: AMAZAZING! We are also going to go visit my family in Canada for ten days. I'm way too excited about this. I miss my family so badly. I want to go back to school. Maybe next semester. Maybe next fall. Not sure when or what for, but I've been entertaining the idea. I've been watching season one of The X-Files. I've pretty much seen every episode already, but I'm enjoying every moment of my revisitation. I love Mulder's character and I love his interactions with Scully. I just LOVE them! Psh! Of course I've documented this summer in photographs. Part One : Newport Beach! WARNING: contains many cliche beach pictures! PREPARE YOURSELF NOW!
on the way to California we saw this... tornado catching team? They only have this fast food chain in like three states, Utah not one of them, so we had it like three times. Some people rave about it. It's alright. The prices are nice. My first ever California sunset Clay and Aria. His dad is the one with the beach house. Clay and Aria were married yesterday and are currently in Ireland. Lucky. We drove with them and had some hella good times. Yes, I did just say "hella good". When we first arrived, we all walked down to the beach. "First time in Cali! Take pitcha!" (Chinese accent) The beach house! Decoration in the window of the beach house... I had never seen jellyfish. There were soo many! This dock was right around the corner from the beach house and we passed it every day. You can bet I was fascinated. Deputy South. She basically hated me before this trip. Now she likes me. Charles!!! Thien (pronounced Tin, not to be mistaken with "Tim") taking photogs. He takes lovely photographs. He did both rafting trips with us. We've seen a lot of each other this summer. He's pretty much awesome. Strange behaviour. He was laying face down in the sand. And he loved it. Happiest child ever. And they called him Sand Beard. These two photograph well. Tin Man!!! Jojo! He's from Thailand. He cooked for us one night and it was extremely good. Must. Have. More. Now. Linzi South. Deputy's mom. Best maternity dress ever. Clark and his friends do enjoy the longboard. "Steph, take a picture of me" Take one...ooops. Take two! That's better! I look weird. Wish there was a third take. Ha. Candy Sorenson, Clarkofcourse, Thien Mike. Charles dad. They went for groceries and brought the cart home. It was later returned. Mexican popsicles! Clark had these all the time when he lived in Houston. They were yummy! Ban mannequin! Teaching people to dress fugly! The water was so blue. Love this picture of Kim. My favourite part of this picture is Thien's face in the mirror. A bunch of us went to the Newport Beach Temple. There was a bunny at the temple. Clark and Carly eating Balboa Bars, which are nothing short of awesome. I used my sunglasses as a filter. Awful. Just awful. Us on the beach. How gay? But how awesome? There will be no attempt to explain this picture. More like "Thousand Steps Turn Your Legs To Jello Beach" The entrance to Thousand Steps beach. There weren't really a thousand steps...i counted... Pelicans!!! Jurassic Park!!! Get ready for the fright of your life.... Carly and her friend, who met up with us a couple times. Gay. Yes, I did. Here's everyone. Except Amy...who I accidentally cut out... Vegas on the way home. Oceans 11! or 12? whichever... wow. that took eight hours to do...

Nicole posted Zach Braff's new years resolutions in 2004.
i went back and found them because i enjoyed them so much.


Zach Braff's new year's resolutions:

Forgo all exercise (including walking),
Learn to smoke (something thin like Capri's),
Take my loved one's for granted,
Stop washing my hands after twosies, 
Laugh at babies who are late walkers,
Pull leaves off trees that appear to be flourishing,
Name the yet to be named voices in my head (something tough like Carl or Kyle)
Be less kind to bunnies,
Floss everything but my teeth,
Travel (but only around my yard and with a light carry-on)
Stop and smell the Rosens. (They're a wonderful family and absolutely compulsive about showering.)

i also enjoy the fact that im posting his resolutions and not mine. haha.
i finished Twilight last night and i must say that i really liked it. i need to get my hands on the next one, like now.

ive had like zero inspiration as of late. BOO. here are some, old and new. some are boring. meh. this page isnt filled up enough. i should start using just half a page. did this on Remembrance/Veterans Day. i like the fist half way more than the second. i took that black and white picture in Ottawa. my husband and i were deciding whether or not we were going to get cable/internet/phone...and money was an issue at the time. we did end up getting them. hmm...for some reason i journal when its that time. weird. like the picture of the matches, love the quote (Farhenheit 451), not such a huge fan of the overall outcome. totally disagree whith the whole evolution of humans thing. wish the picture showed up better. its Bill Cosby, and a quote from the Simpsons. i enjoy this one. i melted crayons for the border. this type of lettering doesnt come easily for me. took FOREVER. White Stripes lyrics. i dripped crayon on this one accidentally. adds character i guess.

this was my first Christmas away from home. it was lovely. i love Clark's family. i miss mine terribly. i took pictures of my gifts, because i am apparently lj-minded... 48 Sharpies(fine and ultra fine!!!)((from my brother-in-law Kenny, we drew names)), Brazilian Nut Shea Body Butter and Body Scrub (smells SOOO good!)((from my in-laws)), the latest Thrice cd (tres bien!), headphones for my ipod (the ipod ones are awful to run with), and a beautiful picture frame! ((these last three things were from Clark!)) The Fifth Element, season one of 24, The Prestige((from my inlaws)), Twilight((from Clark)), and Angel (perfume from my Dad!) GOO!!!! the shoes i wanted from Aldo! i cannot believe that my in-laws bought me these! how awesome are these??? as you can see my shoe addiction has been fed. these ones are from Clarkie! pillow cases from my Grandma, a maple leaf body pillow case (Toronto Maple Leaf colours of course!), a humbug bag (holds all my Sharpies!), and star shaped dish cloths from my Mom! i LOVE homemade gifts!!! a cardinal trivet for my hot pots! GOO!!!! from Mom. Power Ranger pillow case, my sister Rachel and my Grandma made this for me! a reversible apron!!! made by my sweet Mother! a corn bag with frogs!!! i will need this to heat my swollen jaw after i get my wisdom teeth removed! also made by my Mom. A REMOTE CONTROL MEXICAN RED KNEE TARANTULA!!!! WITH A CONTROLLER THAT LOOKS LIKE AN EGG SACK!!! WOWEEEE!!!!! i cannot wait until the spring when i can take it out and control it behind a bush to scare the crap out of people!!! my father-in-law picked this out for me!!! it would seem he knows me well. and a Jack Skellington key cover from Clark! wooooooohooooo!!!!! i will never have trouble finding my house key in the dark again! also, my parents also gave us $100 Target gift card which we spent on a space heater for our apartment, The Office season 1, Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix, and Bill and Ted's Excellent Adventure!!! i forgot my camera at home and we spent Christmas Eve at the Nelson's...you have no idea how angry i was. so yeah, no pictures from Christmas. go me. we got to talk to Chase. he called from Russia on Christmas Eve. it was awesome to hear from him. he is doing really well! his Russian sounds great! Clark's Mom has cancer. its terminal, but we dont know how long she has. its way depressing. she started chemo last week so shes very sick now. she's my Mother her in Utah and shes a really awesome person, its going to be way hard without her. we just hope that she will live long enough to see Chase return home from his mission. in other news, i got myself a full time job at Office Max yesterday! its only a block away! i walked in and the guy gave me an interview in the desk and chair section! the interview went really well. he said that i have the job once i pass the back round check and drug test...yes drug test. ive never had to do that before!!! i go today when Clark gets home to be tested. i had to fill this long application out online last night and then today i went back to do some more paper work. i should start training next week. yay for employment!!!

I wrote this goofy poem for Clark a long time ago. It's completely ridiculous and made me laugh for about an hour when i found it. "Jack-o-lanterns mock and scorn with their fire filled grins. A large array of squash - complete with Jay Leno chins. The purple pimpernel prances along precociously primping previously picked pansies. Bewildering! A goat races a raccoon. Who will win? Why, the goat of course! Without the slightest glimpse at the moon! Paperclips, screws, staples, string, used for holding things together. Mend yourself. Babbling brooks, chipmunks, blossoming meadows. Gay. Use plastic cuttlery to pick apart a mangled heap of lies. The young Mexican dances carelessly in the streets, never missing a beat. To work or not to work? The question that one asks himself as he sits in class. The answer is no. Instead, brain space used for problem solving is taken up by thoughts of formaldehyde, spatulas, hockey pucks, sombreros, and cattle. In times of desperation it is plausible to think of the little purple elastics that are used on stalks of celery, broccoli, and asparagus. Just knowing that if you are purple you can gain wonderful friendships with vegetables must be a comforting thought for an elastic. Plastic cutlery, a mans best friend." What in the hell!? Wow. Just, wow. I am not even going to try and explain this. Clark and I made gingerbread houses! And cookies!!! Clark's! mine! this guy is my favourite. made this one at Clark's family Christmas party! here she is again avec saggy boobs and sans legs! made this sock creature for my sister Rachel for Christmas. I hope she likes it!!! i went a little crazy with the photos of him... her birthday is also this month. i made her this card. She loved it! Rachel: "did you take that picture just for the card?" me: "haha yes!" Rachel: "haha you're so gay!" these are picture from Temple Square. the place looks especially brilliant during December! I LOVE this picture! ...i really wish those people werent standing there. Clark, surprisingly, making a goofy pose and allowing me to take a picture. this was a rare occurrence. I also LOVE this picture! this is pretty random, but, how much does Clark's cousin look like Amanda Peet!? ALOT!!!

HAPPY HALLOWEEEEEN!!!!! Clark had to work tonight. my plans fell through, but i got dressed up anyway, and took lots of goofy pictures. hey, when youre bored, why not camwhore??? actually, im not too sure if there is any excuse for camwhoring... oh well... I'm a bag of jelly beans!!! Clark and i carved pumpkins last night! mines Jack! I did my makeup all fancy and shtuff... this is my duck face. do i look scared??? that was what i was going for...

It's been a while. So here's a bit of an update. Clark and I got married in the Toronto Ontario Temple for the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints on January 26th, 2007. It snowed that day. It was beautiful! Clark and I now live in Salt Lake City, Utah so that he can attend the University of Utah. I love it here. I miss my family and friends a heck of alot though. I'm waiting for my workers permit, so for now I've just been...well...hanging out. Clark's family Clark's parents My parents My family!!! Me and one of my best friends Erin Ewing. Erin's Step-dad and Step-siblings. I grew up with them. Tasha and Brandon Bunnage!!! All of these pictures, except this one, were taken by Brandon. His skills are fantastic. Melissa Popiel. Grew up with her around too. We went to church together. She was my Young Women's leader for a few years. My Mom, sister Rachel and I. Me and my brothers, Nathan ans Trevor. Brother Gilespee! I've known him from church forever and found out that day that he would be the one sealing(marrying) Clark and I. Hahaha. I couldnt resist... ZIE EEEEEEND!!!!

im not quite sure what to do with myself when im not on the phone with Clark. there are alot of things i could be doing, or should be doing, but i dont usually bring myself to do them. i keep missing the bus for school. and then i miss school because my dad wont drive me, even though hes awake in the mornings. i know, i know, wake up earlier. theres a new tomb raider game coming out. i watched the trailer and just about died, it looks amazing. they have this thing called "desktop lara" and she runs around your desktop. i hit that shit up. i dont think having lara run around my desktop could ever get annoying. oh lara. my hero. we had the bunnages over for dinner. it was excellent. spent some time talking to jackie and tash, and playing with Michael and Max. Goo. i cant wait to have kids. jennifer anniston has nice boobs [they are watching Derailed in the next room] this is Clarkie when he was a little boy. Zoolander much?

one day i met a guy named Steve Lynn. He IS very cool.

and now we are friends.

he calls me "Plava"

he put me in the top 12 on his "friendky friends" list on msn.

and then one day he was emo and i left a message on his phone and made him feel better.

the end.

okay so im way too excited for Clark to come and visit me. december 29th isnt coming fast enough... you have no idea how many people have asked me what hes from because he definitely looks like an effing celebrity. soo....we made up an alias, when people ask who he is i simply tell them his name is Lincoln Porter Shembrae and that hes from One Tree Hill. haha. works every time. but aside from the fact that hes incredibly sexy... its not about looks, well you must first be initially attracted to someone, but there are more important things. going into detail on the greatness of my friend would take all day so ill spare ya on this one. but to make a long story short i would suffice it to say that.... HE IS AMAZING!!! thought i would post about him because hes all i can think about right now.

so i chopped my hair again... this is what it looked like before i got it hacked... its not really a fantastic representation but this was the latest picture... and as of 9:30 on this beautiful snow-day morning... I ABSOLUTELY LOVE IT!!!

i should definatley not be up right now. 
i should have actually done my english assignment. eff.

talking to Clark has become an addiction? a necessity? the best part of my day? everyday...yes.
hes a really good friend.
excited for him to come and visit. he lives in utah. which sucks hardcore. december 29. cant wait.

so Harry effing Potter and the mother effing Goblet of Fire!? tomorrow!!! 3:30!!! GOO!
and then...
AlEXISONFIRE at 7:00 at St. Andrews!!! i get in for free and get to go backstage! amazing! 

im gunna pee from the joy of this all. what?

my bed and harry potter quilt are calling me. and yes, they talk. believe it.

Nicole. its effing Potter.
mua ha.ha.ha.

i went to see The Used with Alexisonfire and Underoath a couple months ago. why have i not posted about this sooner? well, because i wanted to wait until i could post the pictures. and now i can. the concert was amazing. i met Quinn Allman and Jeph Howard from The Used. I also met Dallas Green of A<3F. he knew who i was. ill save that for another post...haha. so yeah, i definatley kissed Quinn on tne cheek twice. i needed to get a picture of it obviously, but the first time we took the picture the lens cap was on. eff. so yeah we took it again. how shweet? they were really cool guys. shibby. good times. good times.

so ... thank you martha stewart...? yeah this was her idea. correction. it was the idea of someone who works for her. theres no way in hell that bitch is this clever. definitely feeling this idea. i dont even care what anyone thinks. me thinks it be a mignificent idea. i dont care if it was thought up for a nine year old. eff nine year olds.

<lj-cut text="it was fear of myself that made me odd."><lj-cut> so its definitely 5:00am. suck. i havent been to school since last tuesday. i missed wednesday because i had a dentist appointment...going to school only would have posed as an inconvenience. thursday- i just didnt wake up. its not even like i woke up at ten and was like "oops, i guess i slept in" no.no. i woke up at 1:30. eff. friday i was sick however. i had a terrible migrane wich woke me up at 5:00am and wouldnt allow me to get another wink. i eventually drifted off for a bit but when i did i had a disturbing dream. i dreamed that i was listening in on my brother Trevor from outside a room as he was about to get a tattoo. yeah, a tattoo on his effing face. so im listening outside this room to his excitement and im all thinkin "haha yeah, its going to hurt him! thats what he gets!". but then the artist actually started the tattoo and i could hear Trevor screaming and crying. worst.dream.ever. who dreams that? 

i babysat for Tash and Brandon that night. Max went to bed early so i had alot of time to dick around. (that sounded perverted, i can assure you that i use this expression in a very relaxed way... well, i mean that no dick was involved...)i watched Alice in Wonderland. that movie is bizarre and effed right up. so you could only imagine how much i enjoyed it. i began to have terrible pains in my right ear, you know, the kind where it feels like someone is stabbing you?! i think i must have a high tolerance for pain because it was mighty painful and i did nothing for it...for over two hours. until Doctor Bunnage came home and i had him take a look. it went a little something like this:

Dr. Bunnage- " damn girl, thats one nasty ass ear infection!" 
Me- "eff..."

hung out with Nicole pretty much all weekend, as usual. we spent our time eating subway, listening to music, listening to music and listening to music. we pretty much just listened to music. we discovered Panic! At The Disco. quite incredible. hung out with josh saturday night. watched Taking Lives and Mean Girls. was teased by the very sex appeal of Josh. does that even make sense to anyone??? whatevs, i get it, and thats all that matters i guess. 

guess who payed me a visit in my left ear sunday night??? yeah, yeah, good ol' ear infection. that dick.
so yeah. both ears infected and throbbing monday morning = no school.
tuesday + still feeling like crizzap = no school again. 
the fact that its after 5am and im still up + still feeling like crizzap = probably no school tomorrow ( or today if you wanna get technical)

i actual accomplished something today, despite feeling like le douche. i finally finished Harry Potter and the Half Blood Prince. i liked it. it twas sad. it twas tricky, yeah le trick was involved.

i went for a run. i ran pretty well tonight. my breathing sucketh the suck. i have a small case of asthma. ill be damned if i let that keep me from running. kinda helped me feel a bit better.

i need to read my drivers book so i can get my G1...
i need to start reading the Book of Mormon so i can be finished by the end of the year.
i need to clean my room.
i need to get a job.
i need to eat some candy corn.
i need to write a few letters.
i need to hang out with Kevin.
i need to do alot of things.

i really want to start keeping a journal again. i mean like a real one. pen. paper. ink.
i think its important to do so. i will.</lj-cut>

so this is ashleys fault. she posted this and i wanted her to do it
for me so i posted as well. "becase i HAD to". oh lerve.

Leave your name and
1. I'll respond with something random about you.
2. I'll tell you what song/movie reminds me of you.
3. I'll pick a flavor of jello to wrestle with you in.
4. I'll say something that only makes sense to you and me.
5. I'll tell you my first/clearest memory of you.
6. I'll tell you what animal you remind me of.
7. I'll ask you something that I've always wondered about you.
8. If I do this for you, you must post this on your journal. You MUST.

we had a bonfire at Nicoles. it lasted until 4:30 in the morning. turned out really well, seemed like everyone enjoyed themselves. 
we talked it up, made new friends, made spider dogs, listened to Yango and Hucker tell a story that they swore actually took place - it entailed ice cream, bright lights, power rangers and a psycho old lady who danced around with an accordian...yeah...they lie. it was rather enjoyable though, im not gunna lie. and whats a bonfire without a little dashboard confessional...no? not normal? okay, i know, but still it seemed to fit the mood. Ashley and i stayed up till 6:00am having a "boy talk". "dah deh lookin at meh" haha.

i accidentally hit my friend Eric in the eye with velcro...i felt so bad, even though it was slightly amusing to watch a guy whos over six feet tall roll around on the ground like a little pansy boy. i got to hang out with my friend Josh whos totally awesome. finally met Snezana, who Nicole often talks about, and i can see why, she is one cool cat. we will be having another bonfuuuuuur so im tres exited about that. 

i saw The Island with Nicole. it was absolutley brilliant. humor + action + suspense + EWAN MCGREGGOR =  one sexy combo. i highly recommend this flick.
im going to see Charlie and the Chocolate Factory tonight with Josh. im really hoping i like this movie, im assuming i will because i am a huge Johnny Depp fan and Tim Burton has directed several of my favourite movies < Sleepy Hollow, The Nighmare Before Christmas, Big Fish, Edward Scissor Hands, Planet of the Apes, Batman, Batman Returns, Batman Forever, Beetlejuice, Pee Wee's Big Adventure ( dont be hatin, you know you love it too)> ive heard mixed reviews... im anxiously awaiting Buton's release of The Corpse Bride, Johnny does one of the voices. looks shweet.

on wednesday im flying with my really close friend Jordan to Tallahassee Florida, where he has family, spending the night with the fam and driving to Alabama the next day for a youth conference. im stoked. ive never flown before and this conf. is going to be alot of fun.
we drive back from Alabama on saturday night and then stay in Talahassee until wednesday, when we fly home. the only thing that sucks is the timing of this trip... this week i will be missing four concerts Finch, Emery, Warped tour and Alexisonfire. im bummed most about not being able to see Alexisonfire because its for a tv show and i had a free ticket. A<3F is one of my fave bands and ive not had the chance to see them yet. i was planning on seeing all four shows but i found out about this trip last weekend, BUT i know that i will enjoy it, so im done complaining.

still working on my Harry Potter and the Half Blood Prince. i went to Chapters dressed up with a bunch of my Hogwarts buddies on July 16. we waited from 4 - midnight!!! 
we had a killer time. my friend posted pictures...of both the bonfire and our H.P. extravaganza...ill link it later, im computer illiterate pretty much so forgive me. wondering why im not done the book? im a slow reader and quickly give up hope of ever finishing. haha. im just savouring the magnificence of the novel. and these are not excuses neeeecole! 

j'ai finis. shibby.

its been a pretty good day, despite the fact that the guy i love skipped auto today. i was uber sad. but oh well, i looked like i had come fro someones butt today! blah! soo terrible, im sorry to all of those who were forced to look upon my uggo face today! i think i have carpal tunnel...my wrist has hurt all day long. not good. im rather surprised at how un-tired ive been today, because i went to bed at 4:30 am and woke up an hour later!
i think im going to kill my effin math teacher! i forgot to get a test signed over the long weekend and shes effin makin me write lines! i was like "mrs. why do we have to do this gay bart simpson crap?!"
quite angering! how gay can yo get. oh and she told me not say gay! grrr!

my mother is insane and has turned off the heat and im too cold to sit at my computer anymore... haha

Well, well well....if it isnt another fog day! what perfect timing! i mean , it wouldnt have been a big deal going to school...but meh, more time to study for history. you know when you get up and discover that its a " canceled bus" day, and you get all exited and think to yourself "well, im gunna sleep till about ten, then im gunna get up and eat and watch a movie.." (or something along the lines of being somewhat semi-productive...)and then you just go back to sleep (which is a wonderful feeling i might add) and dont end up waking up until like 2??? then you wake up and look at what time it is and surprisingly youre not surprised...because thats what always happens? well...i know thats what happens to me all the time...and im hoping its not just me. now i wouldnt say i was a lazy person, im actually very productive when im not drowning in a pile of school/play/work/church responsibilities etc. sleeping in is good...but it also sucks at the same time,if you know what i mean. its good to get the rest that youve been missing ( cuz come on guys we all know we need to go to bed earlier) , but once youve slept in then half of teh day is gone. at first youre just like "oh well, big deal", but after the billionth time sleeping in so late it begins to ware you down . sound ridiculous? then youre obviously not sleeping in like me... but i am really starting to get mad with myself...cuz its like holy crap! when am i ever gunna learn that i need to get my butt outta bed, and if i dont then nothing will get accomplished and ill be miserable! never fails though...i always end up doing it...so i need to make a change...like now... because, ill tell you why, my room is a complete pig stye! like its ridiculous! its not dirty...just cluttered with mess and unorganized papers...so that needs to be cleaned...like now...and im behind on too many things....which im not going to list...beacause ive had enough ranting for one day. anyway, my advice to you is : dont sleep in!!! or you will sleep your life away!!!

WOW! finally starting my lj! my friend( whom i love dearly) has been telling me to start one for quite some time now... truth is, i dont really have that much time to write, but i will find some. it was actually my friend who helped me design this page, seeing as how im computer illiterate. so thank you very much V! well done!
stayed at her house last night. good times, listening to tons of "sic beats", and watching Napoleon Dynamite, both with and without commentary. then theres her sister, whom i love dearly also, who we encouraged to jump in the three-foot-high snow, while in her pj's....and she sure did it...cant wait to see those pictures! haha i knew she would do it! love you shley! 
i was supposed to play basketball with the missionaries today...but we were somewhat snowed in...i love snow, but not when it prevents me from playing basketball, and from going to the movies! haha! (dont worry guys, i know your mom was only showing concern for us, no biggy).
oh and V, thanks for the lovely food!!!
ill update later...im too busy!
